## Q22 Optimization Summary

### Performance Improvement

**Baseline (iter_0):** 1548.54 ms
**Expected Performance (iter_1):** ~120-180 ms (estimated 8-13x speedup)

### Key Optimizations Applied

#### 1. **Anti-Join Data Structure Optimization** (86% of original runtime)
   - **Changed:** Sorted vector + binary search → Hash set with O(1) lookups
   - **Location:** Lines 197-214
   - **Impact:** 
     - Old approach: Copy 15M keys → O(15M log 15M) sort + 1.5M × O(log 999K) lookups = 30M+ comparisons
     - New approach: Single-pass hash set construction + 1.5M × O(1) lookups
     - **Expected 10-15x speedup on build_antijoin step alone**
   
   - **Code change:**
     ```cpp
     // OLD: Sorted vector with binary search
     std::vector<int32_t> orders_keys(o_custkey, o_custkey + orders_count);
     std::sort(orders_keys.begin(), orders_keys.end());
     // ... plus O(log N) lookups per customer
     
     // NEW: Hash set with O(1) lookups
     std::unordered_set<int32_t> orders_keys_set;
     orders_keys_set.reserve(orders_count / 10);
     for (int32_t i = 0; i < orders_count; i++) {
         orders_keys_set.insert(o_custkey[i]);
     }
     ```

#### 2. **Dictionary Lookup Optimization** (minor)
   - **Changed:** Repeated dictionary lookups in hot loop → Pre-computed lookup map
   - **Location:** Lines 247-252
   - **Impact:** Eliminates 1.5M × dictionary lookups and string comparisons in the filter-aggregate loop
   - **Code change:**
     ```cpp
     // Pre-extract all 7 target country codes once
     std::unordered_map<int32_t, std::string> target_code_to_country;
     for (int32_t code : target_phone_codes) {
         std::string country = extract_country_code(phone_dict[code]);
         target_code_to_country[code] = country;
     }
     // Then use in hot loop: const std::string& country = target_code_to_country.at(phone_code);
